text: Won Sun-jin (born July 4, 1974) is a South Korean taekwondo practitioner. She won a gold medal in flyweight at the 1989 World Taekwondo Championships in Seoul. She won a bronze medal in bantamweight at the 1993 World Taekwondo Championships in New York City, and a gold medal in bantamweight at the 1995 World Taekwondo Championships in Manila. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1974 births Category:Living people Category:South Korean female taekwondo practitioners Category:World Taekwondo Championships medalists Category:Asian Taekwondo Championships medalists
